article.description: — Chris Maidoh had 13 points off the bench to lead Fairfield to a 72-54 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Maidoh carries Fairfield past Fairleigh Dickinson 72-54
article.linkText: Maidoh carries Fairfield past Fairleigh Dickinson 72-54
article.story: TEANECK, N.J. -- — Chris Maidoh had 13 points off the bench to lead Fairfield to a 72-54 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Wednesday night. Taj Benning had 12 points and six rebounds for Fairfield (8-3), which won its fifth straight game. Jake Wojcik added 11 points. Supreme Cook had seven rebounds. Fairfield totaled 28 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Pier-Olivier Racine had 12 points for the Knights (0-9). Brandon Rush added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
